Certainly! Below is a LaTeX document that contains the poem about a talking tree:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{geometry}
\geometry{a4paper, margin=1in}
\usepackage{lipsum}

\title{The Talking Tree}
\author{}
\date{}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

\begin{verse}
The tree stands tall, its branches sway\\
A voice within, it starts to say\\
"I've seen the world, from up high\\
The changing seasons passing by"\\

The people come, they listen close\\
As stories of the world it knows\\
The tree has watched, as time has flown\\
And in its wisdom, it has grown\\

So come and sit, beneath its shade\\
And hear the tales that it has made\\
For though it may be just a tree\\
Its voice is full of history
\end{verse}

\end{document}
```

To compile this document, save it with the `.tex` extension (e.g., `talking_tree.tex`) and use a LaTeX editor or command-line tool to compile it into a PDF. This will provide you with a nicely formatted document containing your poem.
